00:37:45.739 --> 00:37:47.210
You project it onto two
dimensions.

00:37:47.210 --> 00:37:50.535
You can write a space-time
diagram for yourself,

00:37:50.535 --> 00:37:54.640
and you can explain all of the
motion and all of the things

00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:57.400
that happen by such a curved
thing.

00:37:57.400 --> 00:37:59.420
So, what happens if you jump,
for example?

00:37:59.420 --> 00:38:02.531
In the Newtonian theory,
you jump, you ought to keep

00:38:02.531 --> 00:38:05.399
going straight up,
except that there is a force,

00:38:05.399 --> 00:38:08.519
which pulls you back down.
So, that we understand.

00:38:08.519 --> 00:38:12.110
What happens--how is that
explained in general relativity?

00:38:12.110 --> 00:38:14.684
You jump and you go in a
straight line,

00:38:14.684 --> 00:38:18.342
but the straight line is
through a curved space--curved

00:38:18.342 --> 00:38:21.119
because of the presence of the
Earth.

00:38:21.119 --> 00:38:24.659
And so, it turns out that the
straight line looks like this.

00:38:24.659 --> 00:38:29.009
